## PART VII · THE MATHEMATICAL ENGINE

### The Science Behind Position Pricing

Shadow Alpha uses a **Modified Black-Scholes Model** adapted for sports betting positions:

```
Position Value = Max Payout × N(d₁) - Strike × e^(-rT) × N(d₂)

Where:
  d₁ = [ln(CurrentProb/RequiredProb) + (σ² / 2) × T] / (σ × √T)
  d₂ = d₁ - σ × √T

  CurrentProb  = Live win probability (from odds feeds + our ML model)
  RequiredProb = Implied probability at time of bet
  σ            = Volatility (varies by sport, league, match state)
  T            = Time remaining (normalized)
  r            = Risk-free rate (mobile money savings rate: ~3.5%)
  N()          = Cumulative normal distribution function
```

### Kelly Criterion Bankroll Advisor

Every user gets an AI bankroll manager based on the **Kelly Criterion**:

```
Optimal Bet Size = (b × p - q) / b

Where:
  b = Net odds (decimal odds - 1)
  p = Your estimated true probability of winning
  q = 1 - p

Shadow Alpha Enhancement: We use FRACTIONAL KELLY (¼ or ½) 
to reduce variance while preserving growth.
```

**Example (Your Brother's Case):**
- Odds: 10.0, so b = 9
- If true probability is 15%: Kelly = (9 × 0.15 - 0.85) / 9 = 5.6% of bankroll
- On a 50,000 FCFA bankroll: optimal bet = **2,778 FCFA** (not 5,000)
- Shadow Alpha would have warned: *"⚠️ Your bet size is 1.8× Kelly. Reduce to 2,800 FCFA for optimal growth."*

### Additional Mathematical Tools

| Tool | Algorithm | User Benefit |
|---|---|---|
| Position Pricing | Modified Black-Scholes | Know your position's value in real-time |
| Bankroll Sizing | Kelly Criterion (fractional) | Never over-bet again |
| Expected Value Calculator | Bayesian inference | Only bet when +EV |
| Risk Dashboard | Value-at-Risk (VaR) | Know your max loss at 95% confidence |
| Copy-Trading Scoring | Sharpe Ratio + Sortino Ratio | Follow traders with best risk-adjusted returns |
| Tontine Yield Optimizer | Monte Carlo simulation | Maximize tontine returns |

