## PART VIII · BUSINESS ARCHITECTURE (THE CYCLE)

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[😎 Bettor places bet on 1xBet/Melbet] --> B[📱 Logs position in Shadow Alpha Telegram Bot]
    B --> C[🧮 Pricing Engine calculates live value]
    C --> D{User decides}
    D -->|HOLD| C
    D -->|SELL| E[🔄 P2P Marketplace - another user buys]
    D -->|HEDGE| F[📊 Counter-position created]
    D -->|COLLATERAL| G[💰 Micro-loan issued against position]
    
    E --> H[💵 2-5% Transaction Fee → Shadow Alpha Revenue]
    F --> H
    G --> H
    
    H --> I[📈 Revenue funds AI/ML engine improvements]
    I --> J[🎯 Better pricing = more trust = more users]
    J --> K[🎬 Streamers promote via promo codes]
    K --> L[👥 New users join via invite codes]
    L --> A
    
    M[🏦 Tontine Groups] --> N[📱 Shadow Alpha Tontine Manager]
    N --> O[Smart allocation + yield optimization]
    O --> H
    
    P[🛍️ Buy & Sell Traders] --> Q[📱 Shadow Alpha Working Capital]
    Q --> R[Inventory financing via position collateral]
    R --> H
```

### The Flywheel Effect

1. **Users join** → positions created → liquidity increases
2. **More liquidity** → tighter spreads → better prices → more users
3. **More users** → more data → better AI models → better pricing
4. **Better pricing** → streamer content performs better → more promo codes distributed
5. **More promo codes** → more users → back to step 1

This is the **Amazon Flywheel** applied to bet position trading. Once it starts spinning, it's unstoppable.

